tructure within and around your vSphere environment Bringing consistency to VM provisioning, overcoming “VM sprawl” and resource contention, and simplifying support Optimizing VM lifecycle management, all the way through decommissioning Automating all snapshot monitoring processes and components Exporting logs, finding/deleting orphaned files, and performing other day-to-day tasks Efficiently conducting mass VM migrations Quickly adding vCenter hosts and clusters, configuring shared storage, and adding hosts to new clusters Using vCO and third-party plug-ins to gain “private cloud” benefits and flexibility Networking/Virtualization vmware.com/go/vmwarepress', DEFAULT, '19.79', '304', '2012-02-27', DEFAULT, 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4_EY6RCO0yAC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Automating vSphere with VMware vCenter Orchestrator')ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
