t on, too: "Ramit Sethi is a rising star in the world of personal finance writing . . . one singularly attuned to the sensibilities of his generation. his style is part frat boy and part silicon Valley geek, with a little bit of San Francisco hipster thrown in" (San Francisco Chronicle). His writing is smart, his voice is full of attitude, and his ideas are uncommonly sound and refreshingly hype-free.', DEFAULT, '7.45', '266', '2009-03-23', '21', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=YtE6JJ78XLcC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'I Will Teach You To Be Rich')ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
